sql:
SELECT COUNT(article_id) AS article_count
FROM articles
WHERE year = 2020;

external_knowledge:
- "names and authors of the pieces" refer to the title and author of the articles;
- "overall feedback scores" refer to the calculated average rating of each article;
- The term "pieces" is a general term used to describe articles.

sql:
SELECT newspaper_id, COUNT(*) AS article_count
FROM articles
GROUP BY newspaper_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS article_count
FROM articles
WHERE year = 2022;

SELECT article_id, title, author, summary
FROM articles
ORDER BY created_at DESC;

SELECT article_id, title, summary
FROM articles
ORDER BY created_at DESC;

SELECT title
FROM articles
WHERE created_at = (SELECT MAX(created_at) FROM articles);

external_knowledge:
- "voices in the conversation" metaphorically refer to the comments made on articles;
- "the latest whispers" metaphorically refer to the most recent comments based on the creation date;
- "each story's heart" metaphorically refers to the article itself, implying that each story (article) is central to understanding the context of the comments;
- "creation dates" refer to the time when the comments were added to the articles.
